{"title_page": "Tony Lormor", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Tony Lormor\n| image               = \n| caption             =\n| fullname            = Anthony Lormor\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1970|10|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Ashington]], England\n| currentclub         =\n| height              = \n| position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1         =  | youthclubs1  = [[Wallsend Boys Club]]\n| youthyears2         =  | youthclubs2  = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]\n| years1  = 1987\u20131990 | clubs1  = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]        | caps1  = 8   | goals1  = 3\n| years2  = 1988\u20131989 | clubs2  = \u2192 [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] (loan)       | caps2  = 0   | goals2  = 0\n| years3  = 1990\u20131994 | clubs3  = [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]]                | caps3  = 100 | goals3  = 30\n| years4  = 1994      | clubs4  = \u2192 [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]] (loan)     | caps4  = 7   | goals4  = 1\n| years5  = 1994      | clubs5  = [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]]  | caps5  = 5   | goals5  = 0\n| years6  = 1994\u20131997 | clubs6  = [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]]                | caps6  = 113 | goals6  = 35\n| years7  = 1997\u20131998 | clubs7  = [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]]      | caps7  = 12  | goals7  = 3\n| years8  = 1998      | clubs8  = \u2192 [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]] (loan)       | caps8  = 7   | goals8  = 0\n| years9  = 1998\u20132000 | clubs9  = [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]]            | caps9  = 74  | goals9  = 20\n| years10 = 2000\u20132002 | clubs10 = [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]]      | caps10 = 48  | goals10 = 9\n| years11 = 2002      | clubs11 = \u2192 [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] (loan) | caps11 = 7   | goals11 = 2\n| years12 = 2002\u20132003 | clubs12 = [[Telford United F.C.|Telford United]]            | caps12 = 4   | goals12 = 0\n| years13 = 2003\u20132005 | clubs13 = [[Sutton Town A.F.C.|Sutton Town]]                | caps13 =     | goals13 =\n| years14 = 2005\u20132006 | clubs14 = [[Heanor Town F.C.|Heanor Town]]                  | caps14 =     | goals14 =\n}}\n'''Anthony Lormor''' (born 29 October 1970), also known as '''Anth Lormor''',<ref name=Anth>{{cite news |url=http://www.hartlepoolmail.co.uk/sport/LORMOR-FUTURE-IS-IN-THE.616757.jp |title=Lormor Future Is in the Balance |newspaper=Hartlepool Mail |date=16 May 2002 |accessdate=1 October 2010}}</ref> is an English former professional [[association football|footballer]] who scored 102 goals from 374 appearances in [[the Football League]]. He played as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]], [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]], [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]], [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]], [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]], [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]], [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] and [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]].<ref name=NB>{{cite web |url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player/tonylormor.html |title=Tony Lormor |work=UK A\u2013Z Transfers |publisher=Neil Brown |accessdate=1 June 2010}}</ref><ref name=SB>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=4608 |title=Anthony Lormor |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=1 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Football career==\nLormor was born in [[Ashington]], Northumberland.<ref name=LCArchive>{{cite web |url=http://www.redimps.com/archive3/index.mv?cat=players&drop=playerdetsdrop&play=lorm01 |title=Tony Lormor |work=The Lincoln City FC Archive |publisher=Lincoln City F.C |accessdate=20 May 2010}} Access individual season statistics via Season Stats dropdown menu.</ref> A product of [[Wallsend Boys Club]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wallsendboysclub.org/gallery/ex-players-photos/index.html |title=Ex-Players |publisher=Wallsend Boys Club |accessdate=4 June 2010}}</ref> he joined [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] as a youth trainee. His first-team debut came on 23 January 1988, as [[substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Mirandinha]] in a 2\u20130 home win against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in the [[Football League First Division|First Division]]. He played four more times in the [[1987\u201388 in English football|1987\u201388 season]], and scored his first [[The Football League|Football League]] goal on his first start, in a 3\u20131 defeat of [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.toon1892.co.uk/detail_player.php?id=460 |title=Player Profile: Anthony Lormor |work=Toon1892 |publisher=K.H. Scott |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> In November 1988, Lormor joined [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] on loan as [[Andy Fensome]] made a loan move in the opposite direction;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AWNB:LTIB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=0F90F78328D02C3C&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB57AB53DF815 |title=Digweed's season ends after his groin injury |newspaper=The Times |format=reprint |publisher=[[NewsBank]] |date=15 November 1988 |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> neither player appeared for his loan club's first team.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=2452 |title=Andy Fensome |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref>\n\nLormor signed for [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]] in January 1990 for a fee of \u00a325,000, and made an immediate impact. He scored the winner on his League debut against [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]], finished the season with eight goals, only one fewer than leading scorer [[Gordon Hobson]],<!-- Cited player profile says Lormor was top scorer in 1990/91 as well, but season dropdown contradicts that. The season stats are definitely for all competitions, so perhaps the words mean League goals? --> and was himself the club's top scorer in 1990\u201391 and 1991\u201392. A [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|cruciate injury]] caused him to miss the whole of the next season, and though he returned to the side after 18 months out, he started only nine more games,<ref name=\"LCArchive\"/> and spent a spell on loan at [[Conference National|Conference]] club [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]],<ref name=halifax>{{cite web |url=http://www.halifaxafc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10437~255612,00.html |title=Players on the Move |publisher=FC Halifax Town |date=14 August 2002 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shaymenonline.org/sol/players.php?command=view&id=328 |title=Players: Tony Lormor |work=Shaymen Online |publisher=Paul Holroyd |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050430020130/http://shaymenonline.org/sol/players.php?command=view&id=328 |archivedate=30 April 2005}}</ref> before being released.\n\nAfter a spell at [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]], during which he regained fitness playing regularly in the reserves,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nufc.com/html/fanzine_lormor.html |title=Tony Lormor Interview |format=reprint |work=The Forgotten Imp |publisher=NUFC.com |date=April 2000 |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> Lormor moved to [[Football League Third Division|Division Three]] club [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] in December 1994. In partnership with [[Phil Robinson (footballer born 1967)|Phil Robinson]], Lormor helped Chesterfield to a run of 21 games unbeaten, which would have been 22 had he not missed a penalty.<ref name=Chesterfield>{{cite web |url=http://www.chesterfield-fc.co.uk/page/PastPlayersDetail/0,,10435~342672,00.html |title=Tony Lormor |publisher=Chesterfield F.C |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> According to the club's website, \"the influence of these two on the side cannot be overstated\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chesterfield-fc.co.uk/page/PastPlayersDetail/0,,10435~1332295,00.html |title=The Managers: John Duncan |publisher=Chesterfield F.C |accessdate=3 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004123237/http://www.chesterfield-fc.co.uk/page/PastPlayersDetail/0%2C%2C10435~1332295%2C00.html |archivedate=4 October 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Robinson and Lormor scored the goals in the [[1995 Football League Third Division play-off Final|1995 playoff final]] against [[Bury F.C.|Bury]] that earned the club promotion to Division Two. Injury disrupted his next season, and after a long period playing either out of position in midfield or not playing at all, he asked for a transfer. Lormor did however contribute to Chesterfield's run to the 1996\u201397 [[FA Cup]] semi finals. He scored in the 2nd round against [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]]<ref>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/season-of-dreaming-spireites-1266972.html\n|title=Season of dreaming Spireites\n|publisher=The Independent\n|date=13 April 1997|accessdate=28 September 2012}}</ref> but did not play in the tournament later than the 3rd round against [[Bristol City]]<ref>{{Soccerbase season|4608|1996|name=Tony Lormor|accessdate=28 September 2012}}</ref> as his teammates went on to beat the likes of [[Bolton Wanderers]] and [[Nottingham Forest]] en route to a semi final against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] at [[Old Trafford]]. In November 1997, Lormor joined [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] in part-exchange for [[Dave Reeves|David Reeves]].<ref name=Chesterfield/>\n\nLormor scored the opening goal and added an assist for a second as Preston won 3\u20131 at [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://archive.lancashireeveningtelegraph.co.uk/1997/11/20/813911.html |title=Luton Town 1 PNE 3 |newspaper=Lancashire Evening Telegraph |date=20 November 1997 |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> but only two more goals came from his next 16 appearances, and he was allowed to join [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]] on loan in February 1998. After failing to score in seven games for County,<ref name=SB/> Lormor left Preston for [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] in the 1998 close season for a fee of \u00a315,000.<ref name=LCArchive/> A fee had been agreed the previous summer for him to join Mansfield from Chesterfield, but manager [[John Duncan (footballer)|John Duncan]] had been reluctant to allow him to leave without a replacement.<ref name=Chesterfield/>\n\nTwo seasons with Mansfield produced 20 goals from 74 League games before Lormor moved on to [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] for a fee of \u00a330,000.<ref name=LCArchive/> Recurrence of a long-standing injury meant he was unable to give of his best at Hartlepool.<ref name=Hartlepool>{{cite web |url=http://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/page/FormerStars/0,,10326~1018580,00.html |title=Tony Lormor |publisher=Hartlepool United F.C |date=1 May 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> He spent a month on loan at [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]], but despite both club and player wanting to extend the stay, his parent club were unwilling to let him remain with their promotion rivals.<ref name=Anth/> He made no more appearances for Hartlepool,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=4608&seasonid=132 |title=Games played by Tony Lormor in 2001/2002 |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> and was released at the end of the 2001\u201302 season.<ref name=Anth/>\n\nAfter interest from clubs including [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/scarborough/2068069.stm |title=Walker on the move |publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 June 2002 |accessdate=4 June 2010}}</ref> [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.northamptonchron.co.uk/test-5/Poppies-are-really-up-for.468332.jp |title=Poppies are really up for the cup |first=Derek |last=Waugh |newspaper=Northampton Chronicle |date=26 July 2002 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> Halifax Town,<ref name=halifax/> and [[King's Lynn F.C.|King's Lynn]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lynnnews.co.uk/sport/boro_boy_bid_1_526962 |title='Boro' boy bid |newspaper=Lynn News |date=15 August 2002 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> Lormor signed for Conference club [[Telford United F.C.|Telford United]] for the 2002\u201303 season. He played only five games before injury again intervened,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=4608&seasonid=133 |title=Games played by Tony Lormor in 2002/2003 |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> and in January 2003 he announced his retirement from football because of work commitments.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Football%3A+Jake+King-a096622528 |title=Jake King |newspaper=Birmingham Post |format=reprint |publisher=The Free Library (Farlex) |date=18 January 2003 |accessdate=1 October 2010}}</ref> A few weeks later he resumed his football career, with [[Sutton Town A.F.C.|Sutton Town]], and scored on his debut.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bexhillobserver.net/sport/Football--Lormor-nets-on.263260.jp |title=Lormor nets on Snipes debut |newspaper=Bexhill Observer |date=19 February 2003 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> At the end of the season, having helped the club to promotion into the [[Northern Counties East League]], Lormor signed a two-year playing contract and also agreed to act as commercial manager.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/news/index.php?&newsmode=FULL&nid=10595 |title=Lormor Gives Sutton A Lift |work=NonLeague Daily |date=8 June 2003 |accessdate=3 June 2003}}</ref> He stayed with Sutton Town until December 2005, when he joined [[Heanor Town F.C.|Heanor Town]] as a player,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ripleyandheanornews.co.uk/sport/Selection-headache.1311110.jp |title=Selection headache |newspaper=Ripley & Heanor News |date=12 January 2006 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> but returned to Sutton at the end of the season as a coach.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chad.co.uk/sport/football/non-league-football/lormor_back_with_snipes_1_686614 |title=Lormor back with Snipes |newspaper=Mansfield Chad |date=11 July 2006 |accessdate=24 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nLormor was commercial manager of former club Mansfield Town between July 2007 and July 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chad.co.uk/stags/Lormor-returns-to-Field-Mill.3070165.jp |title=Lormor returns to Field Mill |newspaper=Mansfield Chad |date=30 July 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chad.co.uk/stags/Bob-Gorrill-returns-to-Stags.4266869.jp |title=Bob Gorrill returns to Stags |newspaper=Mansfield Chad |date=8 July 2008 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lormor, Tony}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Ashington]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Newcastle United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Norwich City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Lincoln City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Halifax Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Peterborough United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chesterfield F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Preston North End F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Notts County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mansfield Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hartlepool United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Shrewsbury Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Telford United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Heanor Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Sutton Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wallsend Boys Club players]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Tony Lormor\n| image               = \n| caption             =\n| fullname            = Anthony Lormor\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1970|10|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Ashington]], England\n| currentclub         =\n| height              = {{height|ft=6}}\n| position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1         =  | youthclubs1  = [[Wallsend Boys Club]]\n| youthyears2         =  | youthclubs2  = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]\n| years1  = 1987\u20131990 | clubs1  = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]        | caps1  = 8   | goals1  = 3\n| years2  = 1988\u20131989 | clubs2  = \u2192 [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] (loan)       | caps2  = 0   | goals2  = 0\n| years3  = 1990\u20131994 | clubs3  = [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]]                | caps3  = 100 | goals3  = 30\n| years4  = 1994      | clubs4  = \u2192 [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]] (loan)     | caps4  = 7   | goals4  = 1\n| years5  = 1994      | clubs5  = [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]]  | caps5  = 5   | goals5  = 0\n| years6  = 1994\u20131997 | clubs6  = [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]]                | caps6  = 113 | goals6  = 35\n| years7  = 1997\u20131998 | clubs7  = [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]]      | caps7  = 12  | goals7  = 3\n| years8  = 1998      | clubs8  = \u2192 [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]] (loan)       | caps8  = 7   | goals8  = 0\n| years9  = 1998\u20132000 | clubs9  = [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]]            | caps9  = 74  | goals9  = 20\n| years10 = 2000\u20132002 | clubs10 = [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]]      | caps10 = 48  | goals10 = 9\n| years11 = 2002      | clubs11 = \u2192 [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] (loan) | caps11 = 7   | goals11 = 2\n| years12 = 2002\u20132003 | clubs12 = [[Telford United F.C.|Telford United]]            | caps12 = 4   | goals12 = 0\n| years13 = 2003\u20132005 | clubs13 = [[Sutton Town A.F.C.|Sutton Town]]                | caps13 =     | goals13 =\n| years14 = 2005\u20132006 | clubs14 = [[Heanor Town F.C.|Heanor Town]]                  | caps14 =     | goals14 =\n}}\n'''Anthony Lormor''' (born 29 October 1970), also known as '''Anth Lormor''',<ref name=Anth>{{cite news |url=http://www.hartlepoolmail.co.uk/sport/LORMOR-FUTURE-IS-IN-THE.616757.jp |title=Lormor Future Is in the Balance |newspaper=Hartlepool Mail |date=16 May 2002 |accessdate=1 October 2010}}</ref> is an English former professional [[association football|footballer]] who scored 102 goals from 374 appearances in [[the Football League]]. He played as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]], [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]], [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]], [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]], [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]], [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]], [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] and [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]].<ref name=NB>{{cite web |url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player/tonylormor.html |title=Tony Lormor |work=UK A\u2013Z Transfers |publisher=Neil Brown |accessdate=1 June 2010}}</ref><ref name=SB>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=4608 |title=Anthony Lormor |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=1 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Football career==\nLormor was born in [[Ashington]], Northumberland.<ref name=LCArchive>{{cite web |url=http://www.redimps.com/archive3/index.mv?cat=players&drop=playerdetsdrop&play=lorm01 |title=Tony Lormor |work=The Lincoln City FC Archive |publisher=Lincoln City F.C |accessdate=20 May 2010}} Access individual season statistics via Season Stats dropdown menu.</ref> A product of [[Wallsend Boys Club]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wallsendboysclub.org/gallery/ex-players-photos/index.html |title=Ex-Players |publisher=Wallsend Boys Club |accessdate=4 June 2010}}</ref> he joined [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] as a youth trainee. His first-team debut came on 23 January 1988, as [[substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Mirandinha]] in a 2\u20130 home win against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in the [[Football League First Division|First Division]]. He played four more times in the [[1987\u201388 in English football|1987\u201388 season]], and scored his first [[The Football League|Football League]] goal on his first start, in a 3\u20131 defeat of [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.toon1892.co.uk/detail_player.php?id=460 |title=Player Profile: Anthony Lormor |work=Toon1892 |publisher=K.H. Scott |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> In November 1988, Lormor joined [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] on loan as [[Andy Fensome]] made a loan move in the opposite direction;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AWNB:LTIB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=0F90F78328D02C3C&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB57AB53DF815 |title=Digweed's season ends after his groin injury |newspaper=The Times |format=reprint |publisher=[[NewsBank]] |date=15 November 1988 |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> neither player appeared for his loan club's first team.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=2452 |title=Andy Fensome |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref>\n\nLormor signed for [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]] in January 1990 for a fee of \u00a325,000, and made an immediate impact. He scored the winner on his League debut against [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]], finished the season with eight goals, only one fewer than leading scorer [[Gordon Hobson]],<!-- Cited player profile says Lormor was top scorer in 1990/91 as well, but season dropdown contradicts that. The season stats are definitely for all competitions, so perhaps the words mean League goals? --> and was himself the club's top scorer in 1990\u201391 and 1991\u201392. A [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|cruciate injury]] caused him to miss the whole of the next season, and though he returned to the side after 18 months out, he started only nine more games,<ref name=\"LCArchive\"/> and spent a spell on loan at [[Conference National|Conference]] club [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]],<ref name=halifax>{{cite web |url=http://www.halifaxafc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10437~255612,00.html |title=Players on the Move |publisher=FC Halifax Town |date=14 August 2002 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shaymenonline.org/sol/players.php?command=view&id=328 |title=Players: Tony Lormor |work=Shaymen Online |publisher=Paul Holroyd |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050430020130/http://shaymenonline.org/sol/players.php?command=view&id=328 |archivedate=30 April 2005}}</ref> before being released.\n\nAfter a spell at [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]], during which he regained fitness playing regularly in the reserves,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nufc.com/html/fanzine_lormor.html |title=Tony Lormor Interview |format=reprint |work=The Forgotten Imp |publisher=NUFC.com |date=April 2000 |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> Lormor moved to [[Football League Third Division|Division Three]] club [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] in December 1994. In partnership with [[Phil Robinson (footballer born 1967)|Phil Robinson]], Lormor helped Chesterfield to a run of 21 games unbeaten, which would have been 22 had he not missed a penalty.<ref name=Chesterfield>{{cite web |url=http://www.chesterfield-fc.co.uk/page/PastPlayersDetail/0,,10435~342672,00.html |title=Tony Lormor |publisher=Chesterfield F.C |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> According to the club's website, \"the influence of these two on the side cannot be overstated\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chesterfield-fc.co.uk/page/PastPlayersDetail/0,,10435~1332295,00.html |title=The Managers: John Duncan |publisher=Chesterfield F.C |accessdate=3 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004123237/http://www.chesterfield-fc.co.uk/page/PastPlayersDetail/0%2C%2C10435~1332295%2C00.html |archivedate=4 October 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Robinson and Lormor scored the goals in the [[1995 Football League Third Division play-off Final|1995 playoff final]] against [[Bury F.C.|Bury]] that earned the club promotion to Division Two. Injury disrupted his next season, and after a long period playing either out of position in midfield or not playing at all, he asked for a transfer. Lormor did however contribute to Chesterfield's run to the 1996\u201397 [[FA Cup]] semi finals. He scored in the 2nd round against [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]]<ref>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/season-of-dreaming-spireites-1266972.html\n|title=Season of dreaming Spireites\n|publisher=The Independent\n|date=13 April 1997|accessdate=28 September 2012}}</ref> but did not play in the tournament later than the 3rd round against [[Bristol City]]<ref>{{Soccerbase season|4608|1996|name=Tony Lormor|accessdate=28 September 2012}}</ref> as his teammates went on to beat the likes of [[Bolton Wanderers]] and [[Nottingham Forest]] en route to a semi final against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] at [[Old Trafford]]. In November 1997, Lormor joined [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] in part-exchange for [[Dave Reeves|David Reeves]].<ref name=Chesterfield/>\n\nLormor scored the opening goal and added an assist for a second as Preston won 3\u20131 at [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://archive.lancashireeveningtelegraph.co.uk/1997/11/20/813911.html |title=Luton Town 1 PNE 3 |newspaper=Lancashire Evening Telegraph |date=20 November 1997 |accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> but only two more goals came from his next 16 appearances, and he was allowed to join [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]] on loan in February 1998. After failing to score in seven games for County,<ref name=SB/> Lormor left Preston for [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] in the 1998 close season for a fee of \u00a315,000.<ref name=LCArchive/> A fee had been agreed the previous summer for him to join Mansfield from Chesterfield, but manager [[John Duncan (footballer)|John Duncan]] had been reluctant to allow him to leave without a replacement.<ref name=Chesterfield/>\n\nTwo seasons with Mansfield produced 20 goals from 74 League games before Lormor moved on to [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] for a fee of \u00a330,000.<ref name=LCArchive/> Recurrence of a long-standing injury meant he was unable to give of his best at Hartlepool.<ref name=Hartlepool>{{cite web |url=http://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/page/FormerStars/0,,10326~1018580,00.html |title=Tony Lormor |publisher=Hartlepool United F.C |date=1 May 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> He spent a month on loan at [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]], but despite both club and player wanting to extend the stay, his parent club were unwilling to let him remain with their promotion rivals.<ref name=Anth/> He made no more appearances for Hartlepool,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=4608&seasonid=132 |title=Games played by Tony Lormor in 2001/2002 |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> and was released at the end of the 2001\u201302 season.<ref name=Anth/>\n\nAfter interest from clubs including [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/scarborough/2068069.stm |title=Walker on the move |publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 June 2002 |accessdate=4 June 2010}}</ref> [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.northamptonchron.co.uk/test-5/Poppies-are-really-up-for.468332.jp |title=Poppies are really up for the cup |first=Derek |last=Waugh |newspaper=Northampton Chronicle |date=26 July 2002 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> Halifax Town,<ref name=halifax/> and [[King's Lynn F.C.|King's Lynn]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lynnnews.co.uk/sport/boro_boy_bid_1_526962 |title='Boro' boy bid |newspaper=Lynn News |date=15 August 2002 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> Lormor signed for Conference club [[Telford United F.C.|Telford United]] for the 2002\u201303 season. He played only five games before injury again intervened,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=4608&seasonid=133 |title=Games played by Tony Lormor in 2002/2003 |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> and in January 2003 he announced his retirement from football because of work commitments.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Football%3A+Jake+King-a096622528 |title=Jake King |newspaper=Birmingham Post |format=reprint |publisher=The Free Library (Farlex) |date=18 January 2003 |accessdate=1 October 2010}}</ref> A few weeks later he resumed his football career, with [[Sutton Town A.F.C.|Sutton Town]], and scored on his debut.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bexhillobserver.net/sport/Football--Lormor-nets-on.263260.jp |title=Lormor nets on Snipes debut |newspaper=Bexhill Observer |date=19 February 2003 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> At the end of the season, having helped the club to promotion into the [[Northern Counties East League]], Lormor signed a two-year playing contract and also agreed to act as commercial manager.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/news/index.php?&newsmode=FULL&nid=10595 |title=Lormor Gives Sutton A Lift |work=NonLeague Daily |date=8 June 2003 |accessdate=3 June 2003}}</ref> He stayed with Sutton Town until December 2005, when he joined [[Heanor Town F.C.|Heanor Town]] as a player,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ripleyandheanornews.co.uk/sport/Selection-headache.1311110.jp |title=Selection headache |newspaper=Ripley & Heanor News |date=12 January 2006 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> but returned to Sutton at the end of the season as a coach.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chad.co.uk/sport/football/non-league-football/lormor_back_with_snipes_1_686614 |title=Lormor back with Snipes |newspaper=Mansfield Chad |date=11 July 2006 |accessdate=24 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nLormor was commercial manager of former club Mansfield Town between July 2007 and July 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chad.co.uk/stags/Lormor-returns-to-Field-Mill.3070165.jp |title=Lormor returns to Field Mill |newspaper=Mansfield Chad |date=30 July 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chad.co.uk/stags/Bob-Gorrill-returns-to-Stags.4266869.jp |title=Bob Gorrill returns to Stags |newspaper=Mansfield Chad |date=8 July 2008 |accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lormor, Tony}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Ashington]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Newcastle United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Norwich City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Lincoln City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Halifax Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Peterborough United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chesterfield F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Preston North End F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Notts County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mansfield Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hartlepool United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Shrewsbury Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Telford United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Heanor Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Sutton Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wallsend Boys Club players]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, remove unref height", "url_page": "//en.